<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ901227-0008</DOCNO><DOCID>901227-0008.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Knowledge Data Systems Inc.:   Firm Posts $104,000 Loss   For Its Fiscal 4th Period</HL><DATE>12/27/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   KDSI</CO><IN>SOFTWARE (SOF)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   Knowledge Data Systems Inc. reported a loss of $104,000,or 0.4 cent a share, for its fiscal fourth quarter endedSept. 30, compared with net of $110,000, or 0.4 cent a share,in the year-earlier quarter.   Sales for the quarter fell nearly 30% to $2.8 million from$4 million a year ago.</LP><TEXT>   For the year, the Salt Lake City-based company said netincome, on the strength of an agreement with a hospital chainin Northern California, rose to $377,000, or one cent ashare, compared with a loss of $1.7 million, or seven cents ashare, a year ago.   The company, which provides data processing systems andcomputer software equipment for the health-care industry,said annual revenue increased 43% to $12.8 million from $8.9million.   A spokesman said the increased yearly sales represent adata system and software package accepted for use at 14Kaiser Permanente Medical Centers in Northern California. Themedical centers are units of Kaiser Foundation Hospital.</TEXT></DOC>